{{Han compound|木|乙|alt2=乚|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=wood}}. It represents a thinly shaved wooden tag and, by extension, a tag or document on which characters are written.<ref>Digital Shinjigen 2017</ref>

====References====
{{reflist}}

===Etymology===
; “to die prematurely; pestilence; to die from pestilence”
: The commentary to the ''{{w|Rites of Zhou}}'' by {{w|Zheng Xuan}} says that it is the word for “to die” in the ancient {{w|Baiyue|Yue}} ({{zh-l|*越}}) language, so it is possibly from {{der|zh|aav}}; compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*kc(ə)t||to die}}  (whence {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*k-ceːt}} > {{cog|vi|chết}})  ({{zh-ref|Norman and Mei, 1976}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
: {{zh-ref|Sagart (2008)}} doubts this etymology, pointing out that this word has been attested in classical texts that are not necessarily connected to Yue or the South. He instead proposes that this word may be a Chinese loan in Yue or the regular word for “to die” in the variety of Chinese spoken in the Yue region.

